For the past 15 years, ASP.NET applications have worked pretty much the same way. In order to deploy a new application, you need to have IIS up and running with corresponding .NET dependencies installed.

Back at TechEd 2014, the ASP.NET team announced the next generation of ASP.NET applications that remove the dependency on IIS. We're talking self-hosted ASP.NET projects! We're talking ASP.NET projects that run off a thumb drive. We're talking ASP.NET projects that run on Mac and Linux. In this talk, we'll discuss how your process for building ASP.NET applications is going to change and provide insight into how you'll be able to adapt your current applications to run on this new platform.
